---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description={SITE_DESCRIPTION}
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About</h1>
			<p>{SITE_DESCRIPTION}</p>

			<h2>The stack at a glance</h2>
			<p>
				OpenAgents is organized as a layered stack:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Products</strong> — Autopilot Desktop (WGPUI), Onyx, and related surfaces</li>
				<li><strong>Execution</strong> — Adjutant + Autopilot loop (plan, act, verify)</li>
				<li><strong>Compiler layer</strong> — dsrs (DSPy-style signatures, modules, optimizers)</li>
				<li><strong>Runtime and infra</strong> — tools, sandboxes, logging, provider routing</li>
				<li><strong>Protocols</strong> — Nostr messaging, typed job schemas, receipts</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Core flow</h2>
			<p>
				Autopilot’s local execution loop:
			</p>
			<ol>
				<li>Plan work (DSPy signatures)</li>
				<li>Execute tool calls (read, edit, bash, search)</li>
				<li>Verify (tests and builds)</li>
				<li>Iterate until success, failure, or cap</li>
				<li>Emit replay and artifacts for inspection</li>
			</ol>
			<p>
				Sessions produce structured artifacts: <strong>PR_SUMMARY.md</strong>, <strong>RECEIPT.json</strong>, and <strong>REPLAY.jsonl</strong> (or ReplayBundle) for replay, debug, and audit.
			</p>

			<h2>Concepts</h2>
			<p>
				The docs cover DSPy and the compiler layer (typed signatures and modules), replay and artifacts, sovereign agents (identity, wallet, lifecycle on Nostr), plan mode, full-auto runs, and Autopilot architecture. Terminology and architecture decisions are documented in the main repo (GLOSSARY, ADRs, ROADMAP).
			</p>

			<h2>Where to learn more</h2>
			<p>
				<a href="https://github.com/OpenAgentsInc/openagents">OpenAgentsInc/openagents</a> — main repo: Autopilot, Adjutant, dsrs, runtime, protocol, and docs.
			</p>
			<p>
				From the repo you can run Autopilot Desktop (<code>cargo run -p autopilot-desktop</code> or <code>cargo autopilot</code>), follow the quickstart and installation guides, and explore the crate map and contributor paths in PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
